5000|$|Congestion avoidance: Congestion control {{can control}} traffic entry into a {{telecommunications}} network, {{so as to}} avoid congestive collapse by attempting to avoid oversubscription of any of the processing or link capabilities of the intermediate nodes and networks and taking resource reducing steps, such as reducing the rate of sending packets. For example, automatic repeat requests may keep the network in a congested state; this situation can be avoided by adding congestion avoidance to the flow control, including slow-start. This keeps the bandwidth consumption at a low level {{in the beginning of the}} transmission, or after <b>packet</b> <b>retransmission.</b>|$|E
