3000|$|... e, {{we compare}} the {{operation}} overhead of HT-CAM, TE-CAM, and CC-VANET for {{increasing number of}} PUs in the network. As the number of PUs increases, the more licensed channels become occupied by them. Thus, the number of scheduled OBU pairs at each scheduling cycle decreases {{and the number of}} <b>packet</b> <b>retransmissions</b> increases. As a result, the throughput decreases and the comparative amount of control bytes exchanged increases. These cause the protocol operation overhead to increase with the increasing number of PUs in all the studied protocols. However, the proposed HT-CAM performs better than TE-CAM and CC-VANET because of a higher number of scheduled OBU pairs and lower number of <b>packet</b> <b>retransmissions</b> even {{in the presence of a}} large number of PUs in the network.|$|R
